Arrogance? Check.

76
00:04:58,960 --> 00:05:02,850
Red tie? Check. He even has
billboards with his campaign slogan

77
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:04,010
"Make Australia Great".

78
00:05:04,550 --> 00:05:08,560
Which notably doesn't say
"Make Australia Great Again".

79
00:05:09,540 --> 00:05:12,660
Let's not rewrite history here.
We are, and have always been,

80
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:15,540
a big baking rock full
of huge spiders.

81
00:05:15,560 --> 00:05:17,520
We're looking to go up from here.

82
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:20,580
Make Australia great
for the first time.

83
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:24,650
Palmer has positioned
himself as a political outsider,

84
00:05:24,670 --> 00:05:27,600
despite the fact he was elected
before, in 2013,

85
00:05:27,620 --> 00:05:30,620
and became a joke for being
the most absent politician

86
00:05:30,650 --> 00:05:34,640
and for this moment, where
he either fell asleep in Parliament,

87
00:05:34,660 --> 00:05:37,530
or realized he had to govern,

88
00:05:37,550 --> 00:05:40,590
and so just played possum
until the next election cycle.

89
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:44,530
All you really need to know
about Clive Palmer

90
00:05:44,550 --> 00:05:46,740
is two of his most
eye-catching business ideas:

91
00:05:47,520 --> 00:05:51,640
his failed Jurassic Park-inspired
dinosaur park, "Palmersaurus".

92
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:55,560
And then there's this idea that
he's been working on for years.

93
00:05:55,730 --> 00:05:58,570
The Titanic II will be
a ship of peace.

94
00:05:58,710 --> 00:06:01,660
It will sail from China
to South Hampton,

95
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:05,620
from South Hampton to New York,
from New York to South Hampton.

96
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:09,140
By learning from the lessons of
the past, the spirit of Rose and Jack,

97
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:12,100
Romeo and Juliet
lives in all of us.

98
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:16,960
The spirit of life, the spirit of love,
to dream the impossible dream.

99
00:06:17,110 --> 00:06:19,980
All of us live in time.
This is our moment,

100
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:22,930
it's our turn
to board Titanic II.

101
00:06:23,030 --> 00:06:25,010
Titanic was the ship of dreams.

102
00:06:25,070 --> 00:06:28,150
Titanic II is the ship
where dreams will come true.

103
00:06:29,920 --> 00:06:34,150
That's an incredible idea,
coherently expressed. Pure gold.

104
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:38,160
Except, I do have a few notes.
First, the Titanic, as a boat brand,

105
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:41,110
is famous for two things:
being big and sinking.

106
00:06:41,130 --> 00:06:45,020
We have cruise ships that are
five times the size the Titanic was,

107
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,060
so that just leaves
the sinking part.

108
00:06:47,080 --> 00:06:51,110
I'm not sure how Titanic II constitutes
"learning the lessons of the past",

109
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:55,120
when one of those lessons is sitting
at the bottom of the North Atlantic.

110
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:57,980
Why is one of those lessons
"Jack and Rose",

111
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:01,040
not historical figures,
neither are "Romeo and Juliet",

112
00:07:01,060 --> 00:07:03,110
which have as much
to do with the Titanic

113
00:07:03,130 --> 00:07:05,940
as the Titanic has to do
with Australia?

114
00:07:06,030 --> 00:07:09,210
Their spirits don't live in anyone.
Had they lived, they'd be dead,

115
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:12,060
along with everyone else
on the Titanic.

116
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:16,210
And fifth, the Titanic II.
That's your name?

117
00:07:17,010 --> 00:07:19,160
The Titanic had
two identical sister ships

118
00:07:19,190 --> 00:07:21,190
and do you know
what they were called?

119
00:07:21,220 --> 00:07:23,200
Something a lot better than that!

120
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:29,110
Clive Palmer's Titanic II project
is representative

121
00:07:29,130 --> 00:07:32,100
of his entire political
platform in this election.

122
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:36,040
He's unlikely to win many seats,
his pitch seems to be:

123
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:40,120
"Let's take a historic disaster
and for some reason, do it again,"

124
00:07:40,140 --> 00:07:43,220
"only somehow dumber, worse,
and in Australia this time."

125
00:07:44,210 --> 00:07:46,100
And now, this.

126
